HEADWORD: King Charles spaniel
<hw>King Charles span"iel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A variety of small pet dogs, having, drooping
ears, a high, dome-shaped forehead, pug nose, large, prominent eyes, and
long, wavy hair. The color is usually black and tan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

